1. The Triangle Is the First Stable Structure

In geometry, three points define a plane. Two points only give you a line; add a third and suddenly you have structure.

The triangle is the simplest shape that cannot collapse without changing the length of a side. That’s why:
	•	bridges use trusses
	•	roofs use triangular supports
	•	geodesic domes rely on triangular meshes

The architect Buckminster Fuller leaned heavily on this principle in his structural designs.

So when you say little triangles everywhere, you’re actually seeing a real engineering principle.

