2. Why Triads Appear in Ideas

Human reasoning also tends to stabilize around three components. With two, you only have opposition. With three, you can resolve tension.

Examples everywhere:

Domain	Triad
Logic	thesis – antithesis – synthesis
Story	setup – conflict – resolution
Time	past – present – future
Physics	space dimensions (x,y,z)
Rhetoric	beginning – middle – end

Even comedy follows it:

rule of three — two establish a pattern, the third breaks or completes it.

⸻

3. “Two Playing at Three”

Your phrase is perceptive.

Often what looks like three is actually a tension between two resolved by a third layer.

Example patterns:

A vs B  → mediator / synthesis
self vs world → meaning
order vs chaos → adaptation

This is what philosophers like Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel formalized in dialectics, and why so many narrative engines look triadic.

